# proglang-keywords/powershell-commands.twlist
#
# Windows PowerShell + PowerShell Core cmdlet names and language
# keywords. Source: docs.microsoft.com/powershell, Microsoft.PowerShell.*
# core module manifests.
# notes: cmdlet names follow Verb-Noun PascalCase with internal hyphens;
#   hyphens lex as part of a WORD so `get-childitem`, `where-object`,
#   `foreach-object` admit cleanly. Authored lowercase per dict
#   convention. Function names from non-default modules (Azure PS,
#   PnP.PowerShell, etc.) are NOT included.

# ----- Language keywords / control flow -----
powershell-commands_if               if
powershell-commands_else             else
powershell-commands_elseif           elseif
